            <div type="commentary">
                <head>EFES</head>
                <div type="textpart" subtype="section">
                    <p>The PPRET Inscriptions database was built through the EpiDoc Front-End Services (EFES) platform (<ptr target="https://github.com/EpiDoc/EFES/wiki"/>), the epigraphic specialisation of Kiln platform (<ptr target="https://kcl-ddh.github.io/kiln/"/>). EFES was developed and released in 2017 as a tool for the open source publication of text encoded in TEI XML and specifically following the EpiDoc conventions, that is the international standard for the digital edition of inscriptions (<ptr target="https://epidoc.stoa.org/gl/latest/"/>).</p>
                    <p>The customisation of EFES for the purposes of the PPRET Inscriptions database was made by Irene Vagionakis and implied, in particular, the creation of a dedicated template and the enhancement of the search facilities, including the addition of specific browse filters.</p>
                </div>
